snippet.textDisplay:
I’ve watched this so many times my eyes are crossed at those hip thrusts.
I’m so jealous of his wife 🤣🤣🤣 But seriously. Kelvin has been consistent from day 1. Always smiling, humble, big toothy grin, excellent work ethic, no whinging. And Oti. She is the queen of choreography. She put so many dance moves into that and they flowed beautifully from one to another. It was a celebration of dance and the best show dance I’ve seen on Strictly. Definitely one to be remembered. After Oti didn’t win with Danny Mac, I didn’t think she’d get another good celebrity to work with. But she was rewarded. Queen Oti I salute you. 🙌🏾🙌🏾💕 Absolutely made my weekend. Commiserations to Karim & Amy because they were excellent through the series as well. But the show dance let them down. The public doesn’t get contemporary dance so much.

snippet.textDisplay: It was INCREDIBLE and INSANE (obliviously in a good way)!!! It was like watching a crazy medley of Kelvin's best moments of the dancefloor - his magnificent tango, his flawless quickstep, his entertaining street dance, his lovely charleston, his wonderful jive... I loved so many thing in this showdance - the constant changing of pace, styles and character and above all Kelvin's outstanding musicality and his strong footwork in each and every style in this bubbly and festive mixture. This song always remines me the freestyle of Mark Ramprakash back in season 4. There is something very similar between Mark and Kelvin - the enormous amount of likeability  and the strive to learn and to master the art of Ballroom and Latin dances. This song brought Mark's his victory back in 2006, because his freestyle with Karen Hardy was brilliant, and once again - this particular song, another unforgettably strong routine... and a victory! A 10!!!

snippet.textDisplay: It was like Kelvin's strictly story, I remember Jay Mcguinnes did this and it didn't work, not with Kelvin. Brilliant swivel, lovely woodpecker, great lifts, great promanardes, loved the return of the Jive push ups. Loved the hip action bits, great rythym, and brilliant retraction on the Jive kicks and flicks, loved the return of the Salsa lift too at the end when he backflips her. His topline was perfect and there was 0 gapping whatsoever. Very quick very fast but very impressive. I was actually having to write all those steps really fast as they were going that fast. Like a lighting flash. Oti was brill too. 10/10
snippet.textOriginal: It was like Kelvin's strictly story, I remember Jay Mcguinnes did this and it didn't work, not with Kelvin. His topline was perfect and there was 0 gapping whatsoever. Very quick very fast but very impressive. I was actually having to write all those steps really fast as they were going that fast. Like a lighting flash. Oti was brill too. *10/10*
